不少科學家都希望[[研究|研究]]木乃伊技術。一些科學家更制造出『現代版的木乃伊』<ref name="Straight">{{cite web | url = http://www.straightdope.com/columns/020222.html | publisher = [[The_Straight_Dope|The Straight Dope]] | title = Do Egyptians burn mummies as fuel? | date = 2002-02-22 | accessdate = 2008-03-16 | archive-date = 2008-04-10 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080410062457/http://www.straightdope.com/columns/020222.html | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Capital Weekly">{{cite news | last = Pronovost | first = Michelle | url = http://www.mainecoastnow.com/articles/2005/03/17/capitalweekly/local_news/n6mummy.txt | accessdate = 2008-03-16 | date = 2005-03-17 | publisher = [[Capital_Weekly|Capital Weekly]] | title = Necessity of paper was the 'mummy' of invention | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101106183429/http://www.mainecoastnow.com/articles/2005/03/17/capitalweekly/local_news/n6mummy.txt | archive-date = 2010-11-06 | dead-url = yes }}</ref><ref name="Baker">{{cite book |last=Baker |first=Nicholson |title=''Double Fold: Libraries and the Assault on Paper'' |url=https://archive.org/details/doublefoldlibrar0000bake |year=2001 |publisher=Random House |location=New York |isbn=0375726217 }}</ref><ref name="Dane">{{cite journal |last=Dane |first=Joseph A. |year=1995 |title=The Curse of the Mummy Paper |journal= Printing History |volume=17 |pages=18–25 }}</ref><ref>[http://story.news.tom.com/vw/55939.html?source=HP_STORY 科学家用死尸造现代木乃伊]{{dead link|date=2018年3月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, TOM.COM, 2010年8月4日</ref>。2011年，英國一名名叫艾倫·比利斯（Alan Billis）的計程車司機病逝後將遺體捐給科學家，科學家以古埃及的方法將其製成木乃伊，製作過程由英國[[第四頻道|第四頻道]]（Channel 4）拍攝成《把艾倫做成木乃伊》（''Mummifying Alan''）紀錄片<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nownews.com/2011/10/18/91-2750117.htm|title=英國電視台拍記錄片　找瀕死男作木乃伊惹議|publisher=nownews|date=2011-10-18|accessdate=2010-10-19|archive-date=2011-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111020161138/http://www.nownews.com/2011/10/18/91-2750117.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

製作一具現代木乃伊費用高昂。一具普通的[[現代|現代]]木乃伊成本約67,000[[美元|美元]]。製作一具[[藝術|藝術]]版的現代木乃伊，成本更可超過數十萬美元<ref>[http://www.kalkion.com/articles/modern-mummies/577 Modern Mummies] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111126072912/http://www.kalkion.com/articles/modern-mummies/577 |date=2011-11-26 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.summum.org/mummification/cost.shtml |title=Mummification Cost |accessdate=2010-08-09 |archive-date=2010-08-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100817021556/http://www.summum.org/mummification/cost.shtml |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

此外，[[人體冷凍技術|人體冷凍技術]]亦被一些[[學者|學者]]稱為製作現代化的木乃伊技術的一種<ref>[http://www.fountainmagazine.com/article.php?ARTICLEID=718 The Modern Mummification Cryonics: Search for Immortality Continues] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111126081724/http://www.fountainmagazine.com/article.php?ARTICLEID=718 |date=2011-11-26 }}, The Fountain Magazine</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Quigley | first=C. | title=Modern Mummies: The Preservation of the Human Body in the Twentieth Century | publisher=McFarland | year=1998 | pages=140-145 | isbn=0786428511}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Quigley | first=C. | title=Modern Mummies: 20th-Century Wonders and Beyond| publisher=McFarland | year=1998 | pages=28 | isbn=0736861874}}</ref>。

==自然的木乃伊化==
自然的木乃伊化是在極端的[[自然環境|自然環境]]下防腐及長久保存屍體。一些屍體在極低溫、或酸性、或極乾旱、或鹽度極高的環境埋葬下, 可以自然長久保存。<ref>[https://archive.is/20120722205409/www.americanchronicle.com/articles/view/44197 NATIONAL GEOGRAPHIC CHANNEL INVESTIGATES MYSTERY OF ANCIENT FAIR-HAIRED MUMMIES IN CHINA],American Chronicle</ref><ref>[http://www.sciencebuzz.org/buzz-tags/natural-mummification natural mummification] {{Wayback|url=http://www.sciencebuzz.org/buzz-tags/natural-mummification |date=20130307080703 }}, Science Buzz</ref>像是[[恐龍木乃伊|恐龍木乃伊]]或[[酸沼木乃伊|酸沼木乃伊]]。

==科幻中的木乃伊==
有些科学家希望未來能取得木乃伊的[[基因|基因]]后，透过[[生物複製|复制技术]]，把它们的[[克隆|基因复制]]至新的活人。

==動物木乃伊==
除了[[人類|人類]]的木乃伊外，在古代和現代，均有[[動物|動物]]木乃伊的例子。不少人希望以人工的防腐技術，來保存他們的[[寵物|寵物]]。<ref>[http://ngm.nationalgeographic.com/2009/11/animal-mummies/williams-text Animal Mummies] {{Wayback|url=http://ngm.nationalgeographic.com/2009/11/animal-mummies/williams-text |date=20101028174956 }}，National Geographic</ref><ref>[http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2004/09/0915_040915_petmummies.html Egyptian Animals Were Mummified Same Way as Humans] {{Wayback|url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2004/09/0915_040915_petmummies.html |date=20110629001239 }},National Geographic</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.animalmummies.com/learningfiles/pets.html |title=Ancient Egyptian Pet Mummies |accessdate=2010-08-18 |archive-date=2010-05-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100510154740/http://www.animalmummies.com/learningfiles/pets.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.summum.org/mummification/pets/ |title=Modern Mummification for Pets & Animals  |accessdate=2010-08-18 |archive-date=2010-08-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100820051753/http://www.summum.org/mummification/pets/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

